                <p>
                  Vulcan is a highly reputable brand in the commercial kitchen industry, known for its durable and high-performance ovens. The cost to repair a Vulcan oven can vary significantly depending on the specific model and the nature of the repair. Minor repairs, such as replacing a thermostat or igniter, may cost between <b>$200 and $500</b>. However, more extensive repairs involving electrical components or control boards can escalate to <b>$1,000</b> or more. The availability of parts and the complexity of the repair process also play a crucial role in determining the overall cost. Given Vulcan's robust construction and advanced technology, repairs often require specialized knowledge, which can add to labor costs.
